  "prompt": "What are philosophical quotes?",
  "response": "Philosophical quotes are succinct statements or expressions that encapsulate ideas, reflections, or insights about fundamental questions concerning existence, knowledge, values, reason, mind, and language. These quotes often come from philosophers, scholars, or thinkers and serve to provoke thought, inspire contemplation, or provide wisdom on complex topics. They can encourage critical thinking about life, ethics, reality, and the human condition. Here are a few examples of philosophical quotes:\n\n1. **Socrates**: \"The unexamined life is not worth living.\"\n2. **Ren\u00e9 Descartes**: \"I think, therefore I am.\"\n3. **Friedrich Nietzsche**: \"He who has a why to live can bear almost any how.\"\n4. **Immanuel Kant**: \"Science is organized knowledge. Wisdom is organized life.\"\n5. **Simone de Beauvoir**: \"One is not born, but rather becomes, a woman.\"\n\nThese quotes illustrate core philosophical themes and provoke deeper inquiry into the nature of reality, existence, and human experience.",
